==English==
===Etymology===
Ecclesiastical Latin, from Greek [[αναγωγη]] ‘religious or ecstatic elevation, mystical feeling’, from [[αναγειν]] ‘lift up’, from [[ανα-]] + [[αγειν]] ‘to lead’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ænəgɒʤi/

